title: For Sale:  Savage Model 99 EG .30-30 Win - Spiegel Edition
postcontent: For sale is my Spiegel Edition Savage Model 99 EG in .30-30 Winchester caliber.  This is a pretty hard to find caliber in an equally elusive configuration.  I've even had it lettered by the Savage Historian, Mr. Callahan.  Sale will include this letter.This is an EG model with a serial number that puts it leaving the factory in September of 1937 and going to Spiegel.  It sports a 22in barrel and pistol grip stock.  It's got the Spiegel drill and tap for scope under the rear sight and on the tang.  I've installed a vintage Redfield peep sight and Marbles dovetail filler.  The stock is inletted with a compass on the top rear of the comb.  It's also checkered and has sling swivels.  I wasn't sure about the originality of the checkering and compass but Mr. Callahan assures me that the sling swivels and D&T are correct for a Spiegel model.  He also says that the compass is likely original as well to "give customers a sense of adventure".  I'm not sure that the checkering is original.  It's just not of the quality you think would leave the Savage factory.  Maybe Spiegel had it done later.  Mr. Callahan's letter didn't specify.  Overall condition is very good for an 80 year old rifle.  No rust or pitting and most of the blue is retained on the receiver.  Even the lever has faint case hardening remaining.  The bore is in great shape.  The stock is in good shape save for some nicks and dings due to handling and age.  There are a couple of small chips on thin edges but nothing real noticable.  It doesn't have the "Savage crack" very common to the 99 at the rear of the tang.  There might be a slight one starting but it may just be a scratch.  All numbers match that I can find.  Even numbers on the wood. This is a very nice, collectable rifle with a factory letter.  You probably won't find another one of these any time soon.  Maybe ever.  I'll include a partial box of Federal ammo that it seems to like.  I'm offering this at a conservative price as I can't verify that the checkering is truly correct.  Otherwise the price would be considerably higher.I can email more pictures if needed.  I understand this is an investment so I'll even take requests.I'm willing to travel a short ways to meet.  I frequently visit Topeka and Kansas City areas.  I can deliver to your door in those areas;)  No, I'm not looking to trade unless you have a real nice 6' barreled S&W 25-5.
